SEC. 3. No private enterprise can be a party to the operating contract, referred to in section two hereof, unless he/it possesses, at the time of the bid and award, all of the following qualifications, namely, that such party:

Is qualified under section one, Article XIII of the Constitution to exploit, develop and utilize the natural resources of the Philippines;

Has been engaged in the business of mining for at least ten (10) years;

Has already capital or if a corporation, a paid-up capital of at least five million pesos (P5,000,000.00) ; and

Has available the necessary machineries, equipment, and competent technical staff and facilities for undertaking the economical and efficient development and operation of the Zambales Mineral Reservations and the

Processing of the ores mined therefrom.

SEC. 4. At least sixty (60) days before the scheduled date for the opening of the sealed bids, the Director of Mines shall publish once a week for three consecutive ks in two newspapers of general circulation the call terms for the bid. The Director of Mines, with the approval of the Secretary of Agriculture and Natural Resources, is hereby authorized to stipulate such terms and conditions as he may see fit in the call for bids, which shall constitute the basis of the operating contract to be executed with the awardee, in addition to the following:

The amount and nature of the bid bond to be required;

Submittal of a verified inventory of machineries and equipment, actually owned by the bidder for mining processing and shipping operations and available for use in the operation of the Zambales Mineral Reservation;

Submittal of a verified list of engineers and technical men, actually employed by the bidder, indicating their specialization and actual work;

The minimum royalty on production to be paid by the operator to the Government of the Philippines, and the time and form of payment thereof;

The minimum royalty on production to be paid by the operator to the Government of the Philippines, and the time and form of payment thereof;

That the operating contract shall be for a period of twenty-five (25) years, renewable for a like period;

That the operator under the operating contract shall be an independent contractor and as such shall furnish all materials, labor, equipment, plants and other installations required by the operations and shall be solely responsible for any and all liabilities to laborers and workers as well as to third parties as may result from the operations in accordance with existing laws;

That the operator will, during the first two years, spend yearly a minimum of three hundred thousand (P300,000.00) pesos for exploration, development of, and equipment placed in the Zambales Mineral Reservations and shall commence such development and operation work within ninety (90) days from the date of signing of the operating contract;

That the operator shall file with the Director of Mines in favor of the Government of the Philippines a performance bond in such amount as may be fixed in the call for bids guaranteeing compliance by the operator with each of the terms and conditions of the contract as herein set forth;

That the operator shall enjoy gratuitous use of timber water for mining and processing purposes in the areas covered by the operating contract before such operation; and

That the Director of Mines may reject any and all bids for justified reasons.
